# Integration test: IIfx Floppy Boot to Finder
# Boots the Macintosh IIfx from a 1.44MB HD MFM floppy disk (System 7.0.1)
# through POST + ADB scan + .Sony IOP driver init + SWIM IOP slot-2 floppy
# I/O + boot-block execution + System loader, and verifies the Finder
# desktop appears.
#
# Exercises:
#   - 68030 PMMU FD-bit handling (PMOVEFD CRP / PMOVE TC at $40804C02-$06)
#   - IIfx FMC ROM-mirror invert (phase $90)
#   - OSS interrupt controller (60 Hz pulse, source pending decode)
#   - SCC IOP and SWIM IOP firmware load + behavioural models
#   - SWIM IOP slot-3 (ADB) protocol over XmtMsg and RcvMsg/irSendRcvReply
#   - SWIM IOP slot-2 .Sony driver protocol (Initialize, StartPolling,
#     DriveStatus, Read, async DiskInserted via RcvMsg[2])
#   - $50F1E000 RPU bus-error probe (POST phase $93) so AddrMapFlags
#     bit 20 stays clear and ParityINIT doesn't post the "Parity has
#     been disabled" dialog
#   - Boot-block code at $00400EF6 (ROM version match, _BlockMove of
#     SysName / FinderName / ScrapName, _InitEvents, _InitFS,
#     _MountVol on drive 1, _PBHGetVInfoSync) and the ROM-side System
#     loader at the JMP target $4080203E + region

# Run long enough for the boot to read the System file from the floppy,
# load the boot blocks into RAM, jump into the System loader, init the
# Toolbox, and draw the Finder desktop with the volume + Trash icons.
scheduler.run 700000000

assert ${machine.id == "iifx"} "machine.id != iifx"
assert ${rom.checksum == "4147DD77"} "rom.checksum != 4147DD77"

# Default IIfx slot table seats the same JMFB card in slot $9 as IIx.
assert ${screen.width == 640} "screen.width != 640"
assert ${screen.height == 480} "screen.height != 480"

# fDBInit (bit 5 of $5405 in ADBVars) must be CLEAR after the ADB scan.
assert ${memory.peek.b(0x5405) == 0x04} "fDBInit still set ($5405 != 0x04)"

# AddrMapFlags bit 20 (RPUExists) must be clear — POST phase $93's
# bus-error probe of $50F1E000 should have stayed in the "no parity
# unit" branch, otherwise System 7's ParityINIT would post the
# "Parity has been disabled" alert and stall the boot at a modal
# dialog.  See src/machines/iifx.c (commit a2f2e34).
assert ${(memory.peek.l(0x0DD0) & 0x100000) == 0} "RPUExists bit 20 of AddrMapFlags still set"

# Verify the Finder desktop matches the reference (System 7 menu bar,
# Disk Tools volume icon, Trash icon, gray desktop pattern).
screen.match finder.png

# Bring up the "About This Macintosh..." dialog via the Apple menu.
# Mouse-position writes go through "global" (the Mouse / MTemp lowmem
# Toolbox globals) since the IIfx's ADB cursor-tracking path takes the
# scenic route through the SWIM IOP firmware; the button press itself
# goes through the SWIM IOP autopoll cycle (commit handling implicit
# Talk-R0 polls via the SetPollEnables / PollEnable Flags in
# iop_swim.c's swim_adb_response).
mouse.move 25 10 "global"
scheduler.run 4000000
mouse.click true
scheduler.run 50000000

mouse.move 25 30 "global"
scheduler.run 40000000
mouse.click false
scheduler.run 200000000

screen.match about.png

quit
